Tool Observation: CONCEPT EXPLANATION for 'balancing chemical equations':

Balancing chemical equations is based on the law of conservation of mass - atoms can't be created or destroyed in a reaction. This means you need the same number of each type of atom on both sides of the equation. You do this by adjusting the coefficients (the numbers in front of molecules), not by changing the subscripts.

